/-!
Curated trust-base check for the acceptance gate.

`scripts/gate.ps1` runs this file with `lake env lean` and fails the gate if any
listed theorem depends on a non-standard axiom -- e.g. `sorryAx` (from `sorry`)
or `Lean.ofReduceBool` (from `native_decide`). Standard axioms
(`propext`, `Classical.choice`, `Quot.sound`) are allowed.

Extend this list whenever a new headline theorem or load-bearing boundary lemma
lands. Keeping the list focused is the point: it pins the trust base of the
claims that matter, not every local arithmetic helper. Superseded but still
checked compatibility surfaces live in `scripts/archive_axiom_check.lean`.
-/

